@startuml mesmerize-sqs-enricher-dlq
title Mesmerize — Content Enricher + Dead Letter Queue\nFailure / poison message path · ADR-014 · NFR-REL-01

skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam shadowing false

participant "Consumer\n(any microservice)" as Cons
queue "service.requests\nor service.events" as Q
queue "service.*.dlq" as DLQ
participant "Ops alerting\n(email / monitoring)" as Ops

== Happy path ==
Q -> Cons : ReceiveMessage (attempt n)
Cons -> Cons : Process OK
Cons -> Q : DeleteMessage

== Failure path ==
Q -> Cons : ReceiveMessage (attempt n)
Cons -> Cons : Process **fails**\n(retry with exponential backoff\nper NFR-REL-01 / visibility timeout)

alt Attempts < maxReceiveCount
  Cons -> Q : Return / visibility timeout\n(message available again)
else Attempts >= maxReceiveCount
  Cons -> Cons : **Content Enricher**\nAdd to message / attributes:\n• errorCode, errorMessage\n• failedService, failedAt\n• tenantId, correlationId, messageType\n• receiveCount, lastException summary\n• original payload ref (no PHI)
  Cons -> DLQ : Send enriched poison message
  Cons -> Q : Delete from source (or SQS redrive policy)
  DLQ -> Ops : Alarm / email / Datadog event\n(incident research uses enriched fields)
end

note over Cons, DLQ
  **Content Enricher** purpose:
  make DLQ messages actionable for incident research
  without requiring live debugger access to the worker.
  Still **no** patient identifiers or EHR tokens in enrichments.
end note

@enduml
